parameters:
Thank you for your hard work on the mission. Karin-san has
been wanting to see you as well.

Karin-chan, you're so cute. You resemble Korin-san closely,
so I'm sure you'll grow up to be a beautiful woman.

Thanks to Kotaro-sama, a splendid mansion has been built.
It's wonderful to have a tiled-roof mansion in the village,
isn't it?

It's been several years since the former head of the Fuma
clan passed away--Kotaro-sama has also started to show the
dignity of a leader, which is reassuring.
Welcome back to the village of Fuma, Nakataro-dono.

Ah, Master Nakataro! Last night's banquet was such fun I'm
a bit hungover, but I'll dutifully perform my gatekeeping
duties. Hic...

The key to fishing is not to panic and to wait patiently.
Understand, Momiji?
Is this how it is, Houzukisan?

What's the matter, Aomaru! With such a half-hearted stance,
you won't be able to inflict even a single wound in real
combat. Put your back into it and come at me with all you've
got!

*panting* *heavy breathing*...! Even so, my partner is just
too strong! Ahhhhh-!!

Ufufu... If Kotaro-san desires, I will offer my body to
you at any time\I[15]

I apologize for last night. You drank quite a bit at the
party, didn't you? If you'd like, I can give you some
medicine that's effective for hangovers.

Welcome back, Nakataro-san. Is it true that the Uwagami army
is advancing towards Kanto? Many of the residents of Fuma
Village are feeling anxious...

The water here is so pure that it feels like the laundry
somehow becomes cleaner.

Is this Kotaro-sama? Will you be meeting with the head of
the household?

Kotaro-san, hello Next time, please teach me how to
throw shuriken.

How were things up there? Did you find any fine women in the
capital? Heh heh heh

Karin-san, you were at the banquet, but it seems like your
health has improved. It's good to see you smiling more since
Nakatarou-san returned. You seemed quite lonely after all.

Hey, Nakataro-dono. Last night was a lot of fun, drinking
more than we have in a while. Once I've finished taking care
of the sword you entrusted to me, I'll deliver it to your
home.
They said today's practice is off. How boring.

Was there any trouble in the village? These are suspicious
times we're living in.

"Yes. There is no abnormality in the village. Your family,
Yobirin-dono and Karin-dono, are both well. They have been
eagerly awaiting your return."

Indeed. I should hurry and see them both. It's already late
today. Tell Kotaro that I will visit the mansion tomorrow to
discuss the results of the investigation in the capital.

"Understood. The head of the clan has been looking forward
to meeting with you, Nakataro-dono. He will surely be
delighted by your safe return."

That surprise attack earlier was shocking. You've improved
your skills, Aomaru.

Haha! I've been rigorously training with my sword under
Master Aida for these past three months.

It must have been a tough journey to Kyoto and Osaka,
faraway lands. I'm glad you've returned safely, Nakataro-
dono.

The sword that Master Aida made for me may be unsigned, but
it's well-crafted. It served me well against bandits on my
journey. I owe him thanks.

It's a sword dulled to prevent cutting people, but it might
have suited you well, Nakataro-dono. With your expertise,
even a picked-up twig could become a formidable weapon.

So you no longer wish to cut people down? It's a waste for
such a skilled ninja, seriously.

It's a decision I've made myself. I apologize for being
selfish, but please forgive me.

Hehe--! Then I'll train even harder and become an even more
skilled ninja than you, Nakataro-san!

Hey now, don't get ahead of yourself, Aomaru. If you want to
beat Nakataro-dono, first you need to become strong enough
to defeat me. You still have much to learn.

Hmph! There's a saying that a man can change enough in three
days to be unrecognizable! I'll surpass you both soon
enough! I'm serious!

So, what's the situation in the capital? Is it really going
to lead to war?

...I'll discuss that matter at the Fuma clan's residence
later. First, I must report to Kotaro.

Indeed. Well, Odawara is a massive and sturdy castle. It
won't fall easily. If they come, we'll just have to meet
them in battle.
That's right... Then I shall return to my own home.

Ah, sorry for keeping you so long. Korin-dono and the baby
must be eagerly waiting for your return. Let's call it a
day.

See you again, Nakataro-san! Next time you have a moment,
please spar with me!

--Ah!? Nakataro-sama! I heard from my brother Aomaru that
you have returned to the Fuma village!\I[15]
Is that you, Kikyo? Good to see you're well.

Please! Since you left the village, I've been so worried...!
Hold me like you used to!\I[15]

Hey now! I've never even held your hand before! Don't shout
things that could cause misunderstandings!

But... when I think of you, Nakataro-sama, I can't sleep at
night and end up masturbating in my bed\I[15] I've adored
you since we were children, and it's so frustrating that
Yobirin-san took you away from me... *sniffle*.

Please forgive me. You are beautiful and will surely meet a
better man than myself in the future.

Ah... You're always so kind, Nakataro-sama\I[15] Korin-
san and Karin-chan are waiting for you, so please go see
them soon\I[15]

Indeed. Your brother Aomaru has grown remarkably as well.
The future of the Fuma village rests on you--

I'm home now. Sorry for being away for three months,
Yobirin.

No, it was an important mission. I'm just glad you're back
safe and sound.

Ah, Karin--Father has returned You've grown bigger than
before I left for three months.

Fufu. This child keeps sucking on my breasts so many times a
day; maybe that's why she's growing so fast.

(Even so, she resembles Korin quite a bit. It seems the
bloodline of shrine maidens is strong indeed.)

You've had a long journey; truly hard work. Now then, let me
prepare dinner. Would you like some sake?
Ah yes. My body is chilled; I would like some warm sake.
The boss is waiting for you at the Fuma mansion.
Ah, Chutarou-dono--welcome back to the village of Fuma.

Houchiku-ji, you seem well, which is good to see. I returned
yesterday but was too tired to report in. My apologies.

Not at all. After three months of espionage missions in
Kyoto and Osaka, it's only natural to be tired.

Hmm. They've replaced all the roofs of the Fuma mansion with
tiles, I see.

Yes, while you were away, Kotarou-sama instructed us to do
so. It's become quite a sight compared to before, hasn't it?

How were things in the capital? We haven't received much
information here, so everyone in the Fuma village is
concerned.
Ah... Just between us, it will likely lead to war.

Ho. The army from the capital coming all the way to
Kanto...? That doesn't bode well...

I want to report the details to Kotarou. Can you let me
through to the mansion, Houchiku-ji?
Yes. The lord is in the back of the mansion. Come this way--
--!? What is the meaning of surrounding my residence?

We have been ordered by our lord to urgently request your
presence at the Fuma residence. We will accompany you, so
please.

I'm asking about the reason for this heavy security... Can't
you even tell me that?
Kotaro-sama...! What has happened to you?

Lady, please keep your voice down and stay calm. Now,
Nakatarou-dono, we ask you to accompany us.

...Understood. I will come at once. However, I have left my
sword with Mamoru-dono. May I retrieve it before heading to
the mansion?

...(What does this mean? This is as if I'm being treated
like a criminal.)

...Do not worry, Korin. I will return soon. I apologize
for leaving you alone again, but I entrust you with Karin--

I have arrived at the mansion, Kotarou. You said there was
something you wanted to discuss with me.

You have surrounded my house with your men; this is hardly a
calm situation. What is the meaning of this? I demand an
explanation.

...Before dawn, a fast horse came from Odawara. Two letters
arrived. Both contained bad news.
What, letters...? What is their content?

The first letter is from the retainer of our great lord. It
seems that two nights ago, our great lord passed away.
What--!? The great lord has... died...!?

Yes. With the passing of the peace-favoring great lord, the
war faction has become dominant, and it seems unavoidable
that we will go to war with the forces from the capital.

The second letter is from the elder of Odawara. It contained
two messages. The first is a demand for a hostage to be sent
to the main castle as proof of loyalty.

A hostage...? We have never been asked for such a thing
before? Does this mean they doubt us, the Fuma who have
served Odawara's prosperity for five generations?

Taking hostages is apparently for conducting a siege battle
at Odawara Castle. They have brought battles with formidable
enemies to a draw by doing so in the past. It seems they
intend to follow previous battles' example.

...It's reckless. The enemy this time numbers over 200,000.
They are on a completely different scale and have a
different army size than any daimyo we've faced before. They
plan to attack from Suruga, Kai-Shinano, and even Echigo.
The opponent has subdued up to Kyushu; they are the ruler of
the land, aren't they?!?

That information is unknown to many. They will only find out
when the forces from the capital attack.

And the second message. The brother who brought this
information about the forces from the capital... You are to
be detained and confined, as per their demand.

Detained...? Why? What have I done? What crime am I accused
of?

The crime of being misled by false information and causing
confusion--so it says...

Absurd! For three months, without taking a single day off, I
gathered intelligence and thoroughly investigated before
writing my report. There has never been a mistake in any of
the intelligence I've reported until now!

Those who accurately know the military information of the
capital are a nuisance. Anyone would be intimidated upon
hearing that the enemy has an army of 200,000, and it would
lower morale. It would also make it difficult to take
hostages from the lords and magnates of Kanto. They want to
keep the enemy's scale unknown and sealed away--that's what
this is about.

...! I cannot accept being punished for providing accurate
information! I will go to Odawara and argue my case!

I cannot allow that. Having received this letter, as the
head of the Fuma clan, I cannot let you act freely, brother.
Everyone, surround him--!

...You're going to capture me... your own brother? Is this
your decision, Kotaro?

Kotaro! Don't look away! Do you really intend to detain and
confine me?

...I'm sorry, brother! As the head of the Fuma clan, I ask
you to honor me by quietly being locked up in the cell.
Please... I beg you...!

...Understood. I will honor you as the clan head. I will not
resist. Take me to the cell.
I will escort you to the cell, Chutaro-dono--
Eh!? Chutaro-sama is in a cell...!?

I'm sorry... I only just heard from Houzuki-san myself...
There were three guards in front of the cell, so it seems to
be true.

...How can this be. Kotaro-dono was supposed to be on such
good terms with him. They are real brothers... why...!?

--! I still can't accept this. I'm going to question father.
What crime they've accused Uncle Chutaro of putting him in a
cell... The others won't be satisfied either...

Momiji-chan, you shouldn't come here anymore. You're being
watched... (whispering)

Yes. It seems I'm also a subject of surveillance. So you
shouldn't come here anymore...

There there, don't cry Karin... Your father will definitely
come back...
